## Brief Event Emission Test

```javascript
const EventEmitter = require('events');

// --- Setup ---
const emitter = new EventEmitter();
const results = [];

// --- Listeners ---
emitter.on('data', (payload) => results.push(payload));
emitter.once('done', () => results.push('done'));

// --- Emit ---
emitter.emit('data', 'first');
emitter.emit('data', 'second');
emitter.emit('done');
emitter.emit('done'); // should NOT push again (once)

// --- Assert ---
console.assert(results[0] === 'first',  '❌ first event failed');
console.assert(results[1] === 'second', '❌ second event failed');
console.assert(results[2] === 'done',   '❌ done event failed');
console.assert(results.length === 3,    '❌ once fired more than once');

console.log('✅ All assertions passed', results);
```

### Output
```
✅ All assertions passed [ 'first', 'second', 'done' ]
```

### What it covers

| Check | Method |
|---|---|
| Event fires with payload | `.on()` |
| Event fires multiple times | `.on()` |
| Event fires **only once** | `.once()` |
| Correct number of emissions | `results.length` |
